Um... I'm okay with that kind of thing...
\n<Minato Neon>Well, in that case...
...Saying that, she quickly left.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」
\n<Minato Neon>「！？」
I overtook her and confronted her again.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>I'm definitely not a suspicious person... And it's
not like I'm trying to hit on you or anything...

I start to panic as I fumble around with the
pockets of my jacket, desperately searching for my
business card holder, but it's nowhere to be
found.
\n<Minato Neon>...A new performer?

\n<Sonoda Kohei>No, that's not it! Huh? That's strange... I always
keep it in my inner pocket, but... Ah!

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Damn it... Today was supposed to be my day off...
I left my business card holder at the hotel...

I remember that it was my first day off since
coming on this business trip, and I was taking a
leisurely solo trip around the station. It seems
that... I was getting excited by this unexpected
reunion.
\n<Minato Neon>...Well, you do your best too.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Ah...
She tapped my shoulder and ran away...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Well... Unlike last time when things were hectic,
this time I have plenty of time, so there should
be plenty of opportunities.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Next, I'll follow the proper procedure... Huh?)

I must look quite ridiculous standing here all
alone.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(No, I don't do any pick-up lines... Please don't
look at me like that...)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」

And then... unable to bear it any longer, I fled
from that place as if running away...

Four months ago... When I was staying at the
business trip destination for about three days for
various procedures, I met her.

\#...It was truly love at first sight. I happened
to see her playing the guitar in front of the
station, and I just stopped my feet for some
reason because of my job. But...before I knew it,
I was captivated.

People who were touched by the same strings as me
also stopped in their tracks, in the cold sky
where \# snow began to fall... Everyone was
captivated by her singing.

\#...I closed my eyes. And then...your figure
singing in front of a large crowd became clear in
my mind's eye.

I was too embarrassed to say this to you in the
end, \#, but at that time... I had a premonition
of your shining future.
